entries.title: Where it all began.
entries.content: This all began as a child with just a pocket knife and a stick. Most likely due to forgetting the skewers to make s'mores on a camping trip. I quickly progressed from skewers to makeshift spears as a child. Cause you knowâ€¦ pointy sticks were more fun. This evolved into smaller things such as animals, words carved into decorations, and later into jewelry such as rings and necklaces. I still have some wood from the first odds and ends box with some partially completed projects just waiting for me to resume them. Still have my first detailed project too.

entries.title: Where I am now.
entries.content: Now I am no longer a child or teenager. Time is a lot harder to come by when you have a job and a child. My projects have also changed in scale. As must as I wish to sit and slowly carve away, power tools same time, and allow me to feel like I make progress on my projects even if I only have a few minutes to do something. My son cares less about the tiny animals and enjoys putting together the table and chair made just for his size. My passion for woodworking is still there the projects have changed and will continue to change just as I am changing.
